<p itemprop="description">The head of service transition management provides strategic leadership for all service transition activities across the organisation. They establish enterprise-wide frameworks for service transitions and ensure seamless delivery of new services into production.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide strategic leadership for service transition across the organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish enterprise-wide service transition frameworks and governance</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive DevOps and continuous delivery transformation initiatives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead organisational capability development for service transitions</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Represent transition management interests in executive forums</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure alignment with regulatory and compliance requirements</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Develop strategic partnerships for transition automation and tooling</li>
    </ul>
</section>

